{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Tibetan Buddhism","audienceTags":["tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan","theme:liberation","theme:compassion","audience:meditation","audience:morning"],"sortPriority":45,"groupingLevels":["author"],"groupingLabels":["Teacher"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Tibetan_Buddhism.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Tibetan Wisdom","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","sourceId":"tibetanBuddhism","displayName":"Tibetan Wisdom","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Wikiquote Verified & Evans-Wentz Translation","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":268,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"tibetan-000001","text":"Having meditated on gentleness and on compassion,I have forgotten the difference between myself and others.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000002","text":"In my youth I committed black deeds. In maturity I practised innocence. Now, released from both good and evil, I have destroyed the root of karmic action and shall have no reason for action in the future. To say more than this would only cause weeping and laughter. What good would it do to tell you? I am an old man. Leave me in peace.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000003","text":"For those who do not guard their morals,Prayers are but wishful thinking.For those who do not practice what they preach,Oratory is but faithless lying.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000004","text":"I attain all my knowledge through studying my mind within, thus all my thoughts become the teachings of Dharma. So long as I do not become separated from my own mind, I am always accompanied by sutras. I have realized that all manifestations are Mind, and the mind itself is the illumination.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000005","text":"I pray to all accomplished beings; I pray you to extinguish the Five Poisonous Klesas.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000006","text":"If ones tries to vanquish foes in the outer world, They increase in greater measure. If one conquers his Self-mind within, All his foes soon disappear.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000007","text":"Do not spend your life committing sinful deeds; It is good for you to practice holy Dharma.","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000008","text":"Milarepa in the Treasury of Lives","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000009","text":"Biography on Kagyu website","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000010","text":"Milarepa meets Padampa Sangye","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000011","text":"The Magic Life of Milarepa (1991) by Eva van Dam","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000012","text":"The Sixty Songs of Milarepa","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000013","text":"Text, The Essential Songs of Milarepa in English","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000014","text":"Inviting the demon\" by Judith Simmer-Brown, in Parabola, Vol. 22, No. 2, \"The Shadow\" (Summer 1997) p.&nbsp;12","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000015","text":"Gallery of Milarepa Thangkas by Dharmapala Thangka Centre","author":"Milarepa","source":"Milarepa","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000016","text":"No suffering is self-caused.Nothing causes itself. If another is not self-made, How could suffering be caused by another? If suffering were caused by each, Suffering could be caused by both. Not caused by self or by other, How could suffering be uncaused?","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000017","text":"I, without grasping will pass beyond sorrow,And I will attain nirvāṇa,\" one says.Whoever grasps like thisHas great grasping.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000018","text":"If you think you see bothDestruction and becoming,Then you see destruction and becomingThrough impaired vision.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000019","text":"Due to having faith one relies on the practices,Due to having wisdom one truly knows.Of these two wisdom is the chief,Faith is its prerequisite.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000020","text":"I am not, I will not be.I have not, I will not have.\"That frightens all the childishAnd extinguishes fear in the wise.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000021","text":"Even if you seek to harm an enemy,You should remove your own defects and cultivate good qualities.Through that you will help yourself,And the enemy will be displeased.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000022","text":"There is pleasure when a sore is scratched,But to be without sores is more pleasurable still.Just so, there are pleasures in worldly desires,But to be without desires is more pleasurable still.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000023","text":"Without hope of rewardProvide help to others.Bear suffering alone,And share your pleasures with beggars.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000024","text":"Even three times a day to offerThree hundred cooking pots of foodDoes not match a portion of the meritIn one instant of love.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000025","text":"To those possessed of breeding, learning, handsome looks,Who have no wisdom, neither discipline, you need not bow.But those who do have these two qualities,Though lacking other virtues, you should revere.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000026","text":"The accomplishments of a teacher of ants Are but accomplishments for earning a living. But the study of the termination of earthly incarnation— Why should that not be the accomplishment?","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000027","text":"Although you may spend your life killing, You will not exhaust all your foes. But if you quell your own anger, your real enemy will be slain.","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000028","text":"If you desire ease, forsake learning.If you desire learning, forsake ease.How can the man at his ease acquire knowledge,And how can the earnest student enjoy ease?","author":"Nagarjuna","source":"Nagarjuna","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000029","text":"From my own limited experience I have found that the greatest degree of inner tranquility comes from the development of love and compassion. The more we care for the happiness of others, the greater our own sense of well-being becomes. Cultivating a close, warm-hearted feeling for others automatically puts the mind at ease. This helps remove whatever fears or insecurities we may have and gives us the strength to cope with any obstacles we encounter. It is the ultimate source of success in life.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000030","text":"Ultimately, the reason why love and compassion bring the greatest happiness is simply that our nature cherishes them above all else. The need for love lies at the very foundation of human existence. It results from the profound interdependence we all share with one another.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000031","text":"I believe that at every level of society - familial, tribal, national and international - the key to a happier and more successful world is the growth of compassion. We do not need to become religious, nor do we need to believe in an ideology. All that is necessary is for each of us to develop our good human qualities. I try to treat whoever I meet as an old friend. This gives me a genuine feeling of happiness. It is the practice of compassion.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000032","text":"My true religion is Kindness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000033","text":"It is very important to generate a good attitude, a good heart, as much as possible. From this, happiness in both the short term and the long term for both yourself and others will come.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000034","text":"There is a saying in Tibetan that “at the door of the miserable rich man sleeps the contented beggar”. The point of this saying is not that poverty is a virtue, but that happiness does not come with wealth, but from setting limits to one’s desires, and living within those limits with satisfaction.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000035","text":"Religion does not mean just precepts, a temple, monastery, or other external signs, for these as well as hearing and thinking are subsidiary factors in taming the mind. When the mind becomes the practices, one is a practitioner of religion, and when the mind does not become the practices one is not.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000036","text":"Great wealth can only be obtained through deception and corruption.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000037","text":"I feel that the essence of spiritual practice is your attitude toward others. When you have a pure, sincere motivation, then you have right attitude toward others based on kindness, compassion, love and respect. Practice brings the clear realisation of the oneness of all human beings and the importance of others benefiting by your actions.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000038","text":"It is the enemy who can truly teach us to practice the virtues of compassion and tolerance.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000039","text":"I am a simple Buddhist monk — no more, no less.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000040","text":"Dr. Rajendra Prasad was a true Bodhisatva. His humility brought tears to my eyes.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000041","text":"Don't compare me with Jesus. He is a great master, a great master...","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000042","text":"I believe that in the 20th century, humanity has learned from many, many experiences. Some positive, and many negative. What misery, what destruction! The greatest number of human beings were killed in the two world wars of this century. But human nature is such that when we face a tremendous critical situation, the human mind can wake up and find some other alternative. That is a human capacity.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000043","text":"Reason well from the beginning and then there will never be any need to look back with confusion and doubt.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000044","text":"Human happiness and human satisfaction must ultimately come from within oneself. It is wrong to expect some final satisfaction to come from money or from a computer.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000045","text":"Bodhicitta is the medicine which revives and gives life to every sentient being who even hears of it. When you engage in fulfilling the needs of others, your own needs are fulfilled as a by-product.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000046","text":"It is also possible within this lifetime to enhance the power of the mind, enabling one to reaccess memories from previous lives. Such recollection tends to be more accessible during meditative experiences in the dream state. Once one has accessed memories of previous lives in the dream state, one gradually recalls them in the waking state.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000047","text":"If there is love, there is hope that one may have real families, real brotherhood, real equanimity, real peace. If the love within your mind is lost and you see other beings as enemies, then no matter how much knowledge or education or material comfort you have, only suffering and confusion will ensue","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000048","text":"If you want others to be happy, practice compassion. If you want to be happy, practice compassion.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000049","text":"Within the body there are billions of different particles. Similarly, there are many different thoughts and a variety of states of mind. It is wise to take a close look into the world of your mind and to make the distinction between beneficial and harmful states of mind. Once you can recognize the value of good states of mind, you can increase or foster them.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000050","text":"Compassion without attachment is possible. Therefore, we need to clarify the distinctions between compassion and attachment. True compassion is not just an emotional response but a firm commitment founded on reason. Therefore, a truly compassionate attitude towards others does not change even if they behave negatively. Genuine compassion is based not on our own projections and expectations, but rather on the needs of the other...","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000051","text":"According to Buddhism, individuals are masters of their own destiny. And all living beings are believed to possess the nature of the Primordial Buddha Samantabhadra, the potential or seed of enlightenment, within them. So our future is in our own hands. What greater free will do we need?","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000052","text":"We need a little more compassion, and if we cannot have it then no politician or even a magician can save the planet.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000053","text":"Compassion and tolerance are not a sign of weakness, but a sign of strength.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000054","text":"Each of us has the potential to contribute … You have a great opportunity to make a new shape of the world.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000055","text":"Conflicts do not arise out of the blue. They occur as a result of causes and conditions, many of which are within the antagonists’ control. This is where leadership is important. Terrorism cannot be overcome by the use of force because it does not address the underlying problems. In fact the use of force may not only fail to solve the problems, it may exacerbate them, and frequently leaves destruction and suffering in its wake.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000056","text":"Love and compassion are necessities, not luxuries. Without them humanity cannot survive.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000057","text":"My confidence in venturing into science lies in my basic belief that as in science so in Buddhism, understanding the nature of reality is pursued by means of critical investigation: if scientific analysis were conclusively to demonstrate certain claims in Buddhism to be false, then we must accept the findings of science and abandon those claims.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000058","text":"If science proves some belief of Buddhism wrong, then Buddhism will have to change. In my view, science and Buddhism share a search for the truth and for understanding reality. By learning from science about aspects of reality where its understanding may be more advanced, I believe that Buddhism enriches its own worldview.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000059","text":"All major religious traditions carry basically the same message, that is love, compassion and forgiveness … the important thing is they should be part of our daily lives.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000060","text":"[Tibetan Buddhism is] not just for Tibetans: it can do good for billions of people in our modern world.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000061","text":"The Tibetan state is located between two of the world's great powers, India and China. Good relations between these powers are crucial for world peace. Tibet has an important role to play.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000062","text":"Media people should have long noses like an elephant to smell out politicians, mayors, prime ministers and businessmen. We need to know the reality, the good and the bad, not just the appearance.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000063","text":"The time has come to educate people, to cease all quarrels in the name of religion, culture, countries, different political or economic systems. Fighting is useless. Suicide.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000064","text":"If a woman reveals herself as more useful the lama could very well be reincarnated in this form.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000065","text":"Forgiveness doesn't mean forget what happened. … If something is serious and it is necessary to take counter-measures, you have to take counter-measures.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000066","text":"I think Europe belongs to the Europeans","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000067","text":"Time is always moving on; nothing can stop it. We can’t change the past, but we can shape the future. The more compassionate you are, the more you will find inner peace.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000068","text":"According to today’s reality, thinking in terms of ‘my self, my family, my nation’ has become unrealistic. An individual’s future is now linked to the entire humanity and planet, to a happier humanity and a healthier world... it’s an encouraging sign that young people like Thunberg are genuinely concerned for the future of the planet.... Eventually Tibet may become a desert, some scientists say.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000069","text":"first here, then I think finally here also. And suck my tongue","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000070","text":"On the political front, we have always pursued the path of truth and justice in our struggle for the legitimate rights of the Tibetan people. We have never indulged in distortions, exaggerations and criticism of the Chinese people. Neither have we harboured any ill will towards them. Above all, we have always held to our position of truth and justice without siding with any of the international political power blocks.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000071","text":"As we enter the final decade of this century I am optimistic that the ancient values that have sustained mankind are today reaffirming themselves to prepare us for a kinder, happier twenty-first century.I pray for all of us, oppressor and friend, that together we succeed in building a better world through human understanding and love, and that in doing so we may reduce the pain and suffering of all sentient beings.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000072","text":"When I meet people in different parts of the world, I am always reminded that we are all basically alike: we are all human beings. Maybe we have different clothes, our skin is of a different colour, or we speak different languages. That is on the surface. But basically, we are the same human beings. That is what binds us to each other. That is what makes it possible for us to understand each other and to develop friendship and closeness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000073","text":"Because we all share this small planet earth, we have to learn to live in harmony and peace with each other and with nature. That is not just a dream, but a necessity. We are dependent on each other in so many ways, that we can no longer live in isolated communities and ignore what is happening outside those communities, and we must share the good fortune that we enjoy.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000074","text":"I speak not with a feeling of anger or hatred towards those who are responsible for the immense suffering of our people and the destruction of our land, homes and culture. They too are human beings who struggle to find happiness and deserve our compassion. I speak to inform you of the sad situation in my country today and of the aspirations of my people, because in our struggle for freedom, truth is the only weapon we possess.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000075","text":"Today, we are truly a global family. What happens in one part of the world may affect us all. This, of course, is not only true of the negative things that happen, but is equally valid for the positive developments. We not only know what happens elsewhere, thanks to the extraordinary modern communications technology. We are also directly affected by events that occur far away.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000076","text":"Peace can only last where human rights are respected, where the people are fed, and where individuals and nations are free. True peace with oneself and with the world around us can only be achieved through the development of mental peace.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000077","text":"Inner peace is the key: if you have inner peace, the external problems do not affect your deep sense of peace and tranquility. In that state of mind you can deal with situations with calmness and reason, while keeping your inner happiness. That is very important. Without this inner peace, no matter how comfortable your life is materially, you may still be worried, disturbed or unhappy because of circumstances.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000078","text":"Responsibility does not only lie with the leaders of our countries or with those who have been appointed or elected to do a particular job. It lies with each one of us individually.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000079","text":"I am deeply touched by the sincere concern shown by so many people in this part of the world for the suffering of the people of Tibet. That is a source of hope not only for us Tibetans, but for all oppressed people.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000080","text":"I would like to take this opportunity to explain the Zone of Ahimsa or peace sanctuary concept, which is the central element of the Five-Point Peace Plan. I am convinced that it is of great importance not only for Tibet, but for peace and stability in Asia. It is my dream that the entire Tibetan plateau should become a free refuge where humanity and nature can live in peace and in harmonious balance.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000081","text":"The following are key elements of the proposed Zone of Ahimsa:","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000082","text":"For the stability and peace of Asia, it is essential to create peace zones to separate the continent's biggest powers and potential adversaries.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000083","text":"When I visited Costa Rica earlier this year, I saw how a country can develop successfully without an army, to become a stable democracy committed to peace and the protection of the natural environment. This confirmed my belief that my vision of Tibet in the future is a realistic plan, not merely a dream.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000084","text":"I believe that our Tibetan ability to combine spiritual qualities with a realistic and practical attitude enables us to make a special contribution, in however modest a way. This is my hope and prayer. In conclusion, let me share with you a short prayer which gives me great inspiration and determination:","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000085","text":"Old friends pass away, new friends appear. It is just like the days. An old day passes, a new day arrives. The important thing is to make it meaningful: a meaningful friend — or a meaningful day.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000086","text":"Whether one believes in a religion or not, and whether one believes in rebirth or not, there isn't anyone who doesn't appreciate kindness and compassion.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000087","text":"If I say, \"I am a monk.\" or \"I am a Buddhist,\" these are, in comparison to my nature as a human being, temporary. To be human is basic.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000088","text":"Today we face many problems. Some are created essentially by ourselves based on divisions due to ideology, religion, race, economic status, or other factors. Therefore, the time has come for us to think on a deeper level, on the human level, and from that level we should appreciate and respect the sameness of others as human beings.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000089","text":"This is my simple religion. There is no need for temples; no need for complicated philosophy. Our own brain, our own heart is our temple; the philosophy is kindness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000090","text":"To study Buddhism and then use it as a weapon in order to criticize others' theories or ideologies is wrong. The very purpose of religion is to control yourself, not to criticize others. Rather, we must criticize ourselves. How much am I doing about my anger? About my attachment, about my hatred, about my pride, my jealousy? These are the things which we must check in daily life with the knowledge of the Buddhist teachings.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000091","text":"As Buddhists, while we practice our own teaching, we must respect other faiths, Christianity, Judaism and so forth. We must recognize and appreciate their contributions over many past centuries to human society, and at this time we must strive to make common effort to serve humankind.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000092","text":"Sectarian feelings and criticism of other teachings or other sects is very bad, poisonous, and should be avoided.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000093","text":"It is necessary to help others, not only in our prayers, but in our daily lives. If we find we cannot help others, the least we can do is to desist from harming them.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000094","text":"If there are sound reasons or bases for the points you demand, then there is no need for violence. On the other hand, when there is no sound reason that concessions should be made to you but mainly your own desire, then reason cannot work and you have to rely on force. Thus using force is not a sign of strength but rather a sign of weakness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000095","text":"As a result of more contact with people from other traditions, as time passes I have firmed my conviction that all religions can work together despite fundamental differences in philosophy. Every religion aims at serving humanity. Therefore, it is possible for the various religions to work together to serve humanity and contribute to world peace. So, during these last few years, at every opportunity I try to develop closer relations with other religions.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000096","text":"Some say I am a good person, some say I am a charlatan — I am just a monk... I never asked people like Richard Gere to come, but it is foolish to stop them. I have Tibetans, Indians, backpackers, AIDS patients, religious people, politicians, actors and princesses. My attitude is to give everyone some of my time. If I can contribute in any way to their happiness, that makes me happy.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000097","text":"I don't want to convert people to Buddhism — all major religions, when understood properly, have the same potential for good.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000098","text":"Fundamentalism is terrifying because it is based purely on emotion, rather than intelligence. It prevents followers from thinking as individuals and about the good of the world.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000099","text":"If you think you are too small to make a difference, you have never been in bed with a mosquito","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000100","text":"The Dalai Lama said acts of violence should be remembered, and then forgiveness should be extended to the perpetrators. But if someone has a gun and is trying to kill you, he said, it would be reasonable to shoot back with your own gun. Not at the head, where a fatal wound might result. But at some other body part, such as a leg.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000101","text":"The Dalai Lama in his struggle for the liberation of Tibet consistently has opposed the use of violence. He has instead advocated peaceful solutions based upon tolerance and mutual respect in order to preserve the historical and cultural heritage of his people. The Dalai Lama has developed his philosophy of peace from a great reverence for all things living and upon the concept of universal responsibility embracing all mankind as well as nature.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000102","text":"I don't think China will negotiate. I think they are waiting for the Dalai Lama to die... The Chinese government feels he symbolizes the entire independence movement, and when he is gone, it will go away.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000103","text":"You know, in 1968 I interviewed an extraordinary man. The most peaceful man, the most gentle, the most tolerant, wise man, than I've ever known... So I interrupted him and I asked him: \"Your Holiness, will you ever forgive your enemies?\" He looked at me in amazement. Surprised, perhaps offended, stunned. And with that beautiful, fresh, ringing voice, he exclaimed: \"Enemies? But I've never considered them enemies! I have no enemies! A Buddhist has no enemies\".","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000104","text":"I think the universality of His Holiness' words and teachings have made this so much bigger than just Tibet. When His Holiness won the Nobel Peace Prize, there was a quantum leap. He is not seen as solely a Tibetan anymore; he belongs to the world.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000105","text":"Maybe the Dalai Lama is the only person who is totally honest, and even with him, he's skillful not to hurt anybody. He's skillful.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000106","text":"We used to say to the apartheid government... Come: join the winning side. His Holiness and the Tibetan people are on the winning side.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000107","text":"I give great thanks to God that he has created a Dalai Lama. Do you really think, as some have argued, that God will be saying: 'You know, that guy, the Dalai Lama, is not bad. What a pity he's not a Christian?","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000108","text":"I heard the Dalai Lama say that a British physicist had told him, “Every nation should view every other nation as a domestic partner.” That one small shift in thinking changes everything.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000109","text":"Ageless Wisdom teachings","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000110","text":"His Holiness the Dalai Lama at the Foundation for the Preservation of the Mahayana Tradition","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000111","text":"Tenzin Gyatso at the official Nobel Prize site.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000112","text":"Compassion and the Individual\" by Tenzin Gyatso","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000113","text":"His Holiness the Dalai Lama at Tibet.com","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000114","text":"XIVth Dalai Lama visits Harvard\" (September 2003)","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000115","text":"The Private Dalai Lama\" by Ron Gluckman","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000116","text":"His Holiness the Dalai Lama at LamRim.com Tibetan Buddhist Internet Radio","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Tenzin Gyatso, 14th Dalai Lama","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"tibetan-000117","text":"INDEX OF THE PROJECT GUTENBERG","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000118","text":"EBOOKS WITHOUT LINKED CONTENTS:","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000119","text":"PICCADILLY JIM By Pelham Grenville Wodehouse","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000120","text":"CONTENTS CHAPTER I A RED-HAIRED GIRL CHAPTER II THE EXILED FAN CHAPTER III FAMILY JARS CHAPTER IV JIMMY'S DISTURBING NEWS CHAPTER V THE MORNING AFTER CHAPTER VI JIMMY ABANDONS PICCADILLY CHAPTER VII ON THE BOAT-DECK CHAPTER VIII PAINFUL SCENE IN A CAFE CHAPTER IX MRS.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000121","text":"PETT IS SHOCKED CHAPTER X INSTRUCTION IN DEPORTMENT CHAPTER XI JIMMY DECIDES TO BE HIMSELF CHAPTER XII JIMMY CATCHES THE BOSS'S EYE CHAPTER XIII SLIGHT COMPLICATIONS CHAPTER XIV LORD WISBEACH CHAPTER XV A LITTLE BUSINESS CHAT CHAPTER XVI MRS.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000122","text":"PETT TAKES PRECAUTIONS CHAPTER XVII MISS TRIMBLE, DETECTIVE CHAPTER XVIII THE VOICE PROM THE PAST CHAPTER XIX BETWEEN FATHER AND SON CHAPTER XX CELESTINE IMPARTS INFORMATION CHAPTER XXI CHICAGO ED.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000123","text":"CHAPTER XXII IN THE LIBRARY CHAPTER XXIII STIRRING TIMES FOR THE PETTS CHAPTER XXIV SENSATIONAL TURNING OF A WORM CHAPTER XXV NEARLY EVERYBODY HAPPY CHAPTER XXVI EVERYBODY HAPPY","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000124","text":"PSMITH, JOURNALIST By Pelham Grenville Wodehouse","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000125","text":"WARING CHAPTER XXIII REDUCTIONS IN THE STAFF CHAPTER XXIV A GATHERING OF CAT-SPECIALISTS CHAPTER XXV TRAPPED CHAPTER XXVI A FRIEND IN NEED CHAPTER XXVII PSMITH CONCLUDES HIS RIDE CHAPTER XXVIII STANDING ROOM ONLY CHAPTER XXIX THE KNOCK-OUT FOR MR.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000126","text":"INDISCRETIONS OF ARCHIE By P. G. Wodehouse","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000127","text":"A SHOCK FOR MR BREWSTER CHAPTER III.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000128","text":"MR BREWSTER DELIVERS SENTENCE CHAPTER IV.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000129","text":"STRANGE EXPERIENCES OF AN ARTIST'S MODEL CHAPTER VI.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000130","text":"MR ROSCOE SHERRIFF HAS AN IDEA CHAPTER VIII.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000131","text":"A DISTURBED NIGHT FOR DEAR OLD SQUIFFY CHAPTER IX.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000132","text":"A LETTER FROM PARKER CHAPTER X.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000133","text":"DOING FATHER A BIT OF GOOD CHAPTER XI.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000134","text":"SALVATORE CHOOSES THE WRONG MOMENT CHAPTER XII.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000135","text":"BRIGHT EYES�AND A FLY CHAPTER XIII.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000136","text":"RALLYING ROUND PERCY CHAPTER XIV.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000137","text":"THE SAD CASE OF LOONEY BIDDLE CHAPTER XV.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000138","text":"ARCHIE ACCEPTS A SITUATION CHAPTER XVII.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000139","text":"BROTHER BILL'S ROMANCE CHAPTER XVIII.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000140","text":"THE SAUSAGE CHAPPIE CHAPTER XIX.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000141","text":"REGGIE COMES TO LIFE CHAPTER XX.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000142","text":"THE-SAUSAGE-CHAPPIE-CLICKS CHAPTER XXI.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000143","text":"WASHY STEPS INTO THE HALL OF FAME CHAPTER XXIII.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000144","text":"THE MELTING OF MR CONNOLLY CHAPTER XXV.","author":"Padmasambhava","source":"The Tibetan Book of the Dead — Evans-Wentz (1927)","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:liberation","theme:liberation,compassion","tradition:buddhism","tradition:tibetan"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"tibetan-000145","text":"THE WIGMORE VENUS 